'''2020年馬利政變'''（{{lang-fr|coup d'État de 2020 au Mali}}）為2020年8月18日[[馬利武裝部隊|馬利武裝部隊]]於[[馬利共和國|馬利共和國]]首都[[巴馬科|巴馬科]]發動的[[軍事政變|軍事政變]]。<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Gunfire heard at Mali army base, warnings of possible mutiny|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/08/gunfire-heard-mali-army-base-warnings-mutiny-200818111723901.html|access-date=2020-08-18|website=www.aljazeera.com|archive-date=2020-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818190249/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/08/gunfire-heard-mali-army-base-warnings-mutiny-200818111723901.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>輕型卡車上的士兵衝進了[[卡蒂|卡蒂]]鎮的桑迪亞塔軍事基地，從軍械庫分發武器並逮捕高級官員。<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|last=Welle (www.dw.com)|first=Deutsche|title=Possible coup underway in Mali {{!}} DW {{!}} 18.08.2020|url=https://www.dw.com/en/possible-coup-underway-in-mali/a-54608009|access-date=2020-08-18|website=DW.COM|language=en-GB|archive-date=2020-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818210130/https://www.dw.com/en/mali-president-prime-minister-detained-by-mutinous-soldiers/a-54608009/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|date=2020-08-18|title=Mali: Gunfire heard at Kati military camp near Bamako|language=en-US|work=The Africa Report.com|url=https://www.theafricareport.com/38039/mali-gunfire-heard-at-kati-military-camp-near-bamako/|access-date=2020-08-18|archive-date=2020-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818190254/https://www.theafricareport.com/38039/mali-gunfire-heard-at-kati-military-camp-near-bamako/|dead-url=no}}</ref>在該鎮的街道上看到了[[坦克|坦克]]和[[裝甲車|裝甲車]]，<ref>{{Cite web|date=2020-08-18|title=Mali soldiers detain senior officers in apparent mutiny|url=https://apnews.com/54737684e3e2a84f9b44656de7343e56|access-date=2020-08-18|website=AP NEWS|archive-date=2020-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818190257/https://apnews.com/54737684e3e2a84f9b44656de7343e56|dead-url=no}}</ref>以及前往首都[[巴馬科|巴馬科]]的軍用卡車。<ref name=":2" />叛軍逮捕了幾位政府官員，包括[[馬里總統|總統]][[易卜拉欣·布巴卡爾·凱塔|易卜拉欣·布巴卡爾·凱塔]]，稍晚總統宣布辭職並同時解散了政府和議會。<ref>{{Cite news|date=2020-08-19|title=Mali president resigns after detention by military, deepening crisis|language=en|work=Reuters|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mali-security-idUSKCN25E1AF|access-date=2020-08-19|archive-date=2020-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818193052/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mali-security-idUSKCN25E1AF|dead-url=no}}</ref>這是[[馬利共和國|馬利共和國]]近十年以來的第二次政變。

==背景==
{{main|2020年马里抗议活动}}
马里的抗议活动自6月5日起一直在进行着，抗议者对眼下的[[马里北部冲突|叛乱]]、政府的腐败和经济的不景气感到不满，<ref>{{Cite news|date=2020-08-18|title=Factbox: Why Mali is in turmoil again|language=en|work=Reuters|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-mali-politics-protests-factbox-idUKKCN25E1LA|accessdate=2020-08-18|archive-date=2020-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819135354/https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-mali-politics-protests-factbox-idUKKCN25E1LA|dead-url=no}}</ref>呼吁[[馬里總統|总统]][[易卜拉欣·布巴卡爾·凱塔|易卜拉欣·布巴卡尔·凯塔]]辞职。<ref>{{Cite news|author=Maclean|first=Ruth|date=2020-07-16|title=Anger at Mali’s President Rises After Security Forces Kill Protesters|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/07/16/world/africa/mali-protesters-killed-keita.html|accessdate=2020-07-17|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2020-07-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200728065921/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/07/16/world/africa/mali-protesters-killed-keita.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|date=2020-07-17|title=Mali PM apologises for security force 'excesses' during protests|work=Reuters|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mali-politics-idUSKCN24I1P0|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2020-07-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200719225849/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mali-politics-idUSKCN24I1P0|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Mali opposition leaders freed after days of anti-gov't protests|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/07/mali-opposition-leaders-freed-days-anti-gov-protests-200714065503441.html|accessdate=2020-07-17|work=www.aljazeera.com|archive-date=2020-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200810030618/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/07/mali-opposition-leaders-freed-days-anti-gov-protests-200714065503441.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Calls for calm as Mali gov't criticised for response to protests|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/07/calls-calm-mali-gov-criticised-response-protests-200713092657817.html|accessdate=2020-07-17|work=www.aljazeera.com|archive-date=2020-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200810030620/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/07/calls-calm-mali-gov-criticised-response-protests-200713092657817.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|date=2020-07-12|title=Mali president dissolves top court amid unrest|work=BBC News|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-53378433|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2020-07-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200731211418/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-53378433|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==政變過程==
由上校迪奥（Diaw）、上校卡马拉（Camara）和将军登贝莱（Cheick Fantamadi Dembele）领导的叛变分子<ref>{{Cite web|title=马里反叛军人领袖称已逮捕总统和总理|url=http://sputniknews.cn/politics/202008191031987560/|accessdate=2020-08-19|work=sputniknews.cn|language=zh-Hans|archive-date=2020-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819110226/http://sputniknews.cn/politics/202008191031987560/|dead-url=no}}</ref>逮捕了外交部长蒂耶比莱·德拉梅和经济与财政部长阿卜杜拉耶·达菲<ref>{{Cite web|title=马里发生军事政变：士兵逮捕政府高官，中使馆发紧急提醒_消息|url=http://www.sohu.com/a/413762387_260616|accessdate=2020-08-19|work=www.sohu.com|language=en}}</ref>。总理[[布布·西塞|布布·西塞]]呼吁与叛变分子通过对话消除隔阂。<ref name=":3">{{Cite news|title=Mutinying soldiers say they have detained Mali's President Keita, Prime Minister Cisse|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200818-ecowas-calls-on-mali-soldiers-to-end-the-mutiny|accessdate=2020-08-18|work=[[France24|France24]]|date=2020-08-18|archive-date=2020-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819020517/https://www.france24.com/en/20200818-ecowas-calls-on-mali-soldiers-to-end-the-mutiny|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=马里总理呼吁通过对话消除隔阂_兵变|url=http://www.sohu.com/a/413801032_115239|accessdate=2020-08-19|work=www.sohu.com|language=en}}</ref>总统凯塔和总理西塞后来在首都[[巴马科|巴马科]]的住所被捕。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Soldiers take up arms as Mali crisis deepens: Live updates|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/08/soldiers-arms-mali-crisis-deepens-live-updates-200818124326841.html|accessdate=2020-08-18|work=www.aljazeera.com|archive-date=2020-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818210142/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/08/soldiers-arms-mali-crisis-deepens-live-updates-200818124326841.html/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=Kelly|first=Jeremy|title=Mali PM and president under arrest, claim army mutineers|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/mali-pm-and-president-under-arrest-claim-army-mutineers-nf6x5qv0b|accessdate=2020-08-18|work=[[The_Times|The Times]]|date=2020-08-18|archive-date=2020-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200826200357/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/mali-pm-and-president-under-arrest-claim-army-mutineers-nf6x5qv0b|dead-url=no}}</ref>

隨著政變的消息傳開，數百名抗議者聚集在[[巴馬科|巴馬科]]的獨立紀念碑上，要求總統辭職<ref>{{Cite web|title=马里发生军事政变总统总理被捕 欧盟非盟谴责 安理会将召开紧急会议|url=https://www.rfi.fr/cn/中国/20200818-马里发生军事政变总统总理被捕-欧盟非盟谴责-安理会将召开紧急会议|accessdate=2020-08-19|date=2020-08-18|work=RFI - 法国国际广播电台|language=zh-Hans|archive-date=2020-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819074409/https://www.rfi.fr/cn/%E4%B8%AD%E5%9B%BD/20200818-%E9%A9%AC%E9%87%8C%E5%8F%91%E7%94%9F%E5%86%9B%E4%BA%8B%E6%94%BF%E5%8F%98%E6%80%BB%E7%BB%9F%E6%80%BB%E7%90%86%E8%A2%AB%E6%8D%95-%E6%AC%A7%E7%9B%9F%E9%9D%9E%E7%9B%9F%E8%B0%B4%E8%B4%A3-%E5%AE%89%E7%90%86%E4%BC%9A%E5%B0%86%E5%8F%AC%E5%BC%80%E7%B4%A7%E6%80%A5%E4%BC%9A%E8%AE%AE|dead-url=no}}</ref>。有示威者将马里司法部一建筑物纵火焚烧<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mali president resigned after troops reportedly arrested him|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/08/18/africa/mali-unrest-troops-president-intl/index.html|accessdate=2020-08-19|last=Rahim|first=Melissa Bell, Mamadou Tapily and Zamira|work=CNN|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125055406/https://www.cnn.com/2020/08/18/africa/mali-unrest-troops-president-intl/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

目前尚不清楚有多少士兵參與叛變。<ref>{{Cite news|date=2020-08-19|title=Mali's president resigns and dissolves parliament|language=en-GB|work=BBC News|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-53830348|access-date=2020-08-19|archive-date=2020-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819050422/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-53830348|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==後續==
[[馬里總統|馬利總統]][[易卜拉欣·布巴卡爾·凱塔|凱塔]]宣布辞职，同时解散了政府和议会。他补充说：“我不希望为了继续掌权，而发生流血牺牲事件。”<ref>{{Cite news|date=2020-08-19|title=Mali's president resigns and dissolves parliament|language=en-GB|work=BBC News|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-53830348|accessdate=2020-08-19|archive-date=2020-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819050422/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-53830348|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=外媒：马里总统宣布辞职，此前因国内哗变被扣留--国际--人民网|url=http://m.people.cn/n4/2020/0819/c57-14352263.html|accessdate=2020-08-19|work=m.people.cn}}</ref>

政变军人组成的[[致敬人民全国委员会|致敬人民全国委员会]]承诺凯塔下台后会举行新的选举<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mali coup leaders promise new elections as detained Keita steps down|url=https://www.rfi.fr/en/africa/20200819-mali-coup-leaders-promise-new-elections-detained-president-ibrahim-boubacar-keita-steps-down|accessdate=2020-08-19|date=2020-08-19|work=RFI|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125200339/https://www.rfi.fr/en/africa/20200819-mali-coup-leaders-promise-new-elections-detained-president-ibrahim-boubacar-keita-steps-down|dead-url=no}}</ref>。CNSP发言人Ismael Wague少校宣布关闭陆空边境，晚9时至次日5时实施宵禁<ref>{{Cite web|title=中国驻马里大使馆发布关于当前马里局势的最新提醒|url=https://news.sina.com.cn/c/2020-08-19/doc-iivhvpwy1909208.shtml|accessdate=2020-08-19|date=2020-08-19|last=央视|work=news.sina.com.cn}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Mali's President resigns after he was arrested in a military coup|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/08/18/africa/mali-unrest-troops-president-intl/index.html|accessdate=2020-08-19|last=CNN|first=Melissa Bell, Mamadou Tapily, Zamira Rahim and Helen Regan|work=CNN|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125055406/https://www.cnn.com/2020/08/18/africa/mali-unrest-troops-president-intl/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

